<section xml:id="sec-polyhedra-semiregular" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Semiregular Polyhedra</title>
    <subsection>
        <title>Defining Semiregular Polyhedra</title>
        <p>
            We now extend our collection of polyhedra by exploring what it means for 
            a polyhedron to be semiregular and to construct some examples.
        </p>
        <definition>
            <idx><h>semiregular</h><h>polyhedron</h></idx>
            <idx><h>polyhedron</h><h>semiregular</h></idx>
            <idx><h>vertex arrangement</h><h>polyhedron</h></idx>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A polyhedron is <term>semiregular</term> if it satisfies the 
                    following conditions:
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Every face is a regular polygon.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            At least two polygonal faces have a different number of sides.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The arrangement of polygons at every vertex of the
                            polyhedron are the same.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>
        
    </subsection>
</section>